<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 6:42PM CDT  by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Forrest,
southeastern Covington, Lamar and southern Jones Counties through 745
PM CDT...
At 642 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sunrise, or near Petal, moving southwest at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Petal and Sunrise around 650 PM CDT.
Mclaurin around 715 PM CDT.
Oak Grove around 730 PM CDT.
Purvis, Pine Ridge and Rock Hill around 745 PM CDT.
Other locations impacted by this storm include Seminary and Corinth.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
